.TH GitAnalyser 1 "October 2024" "GitAnalyser 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
GitAnalyser \- extract productivity metrics from git repositories and visualize them
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B GitAnalyser
[\fB\-\-port\fR \fIPORT\fR] [\fB\-p\fR, \fB\-\-path\fR \fIPATH\fR] [\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B GitAnalyser
reads your local git repository's commit history and file structures to calculate important productivity and code-base metrics.
It starts a local web server (defaulting to port 8080) and provides an interactive, neon-styled web dashboard where you can see:
.PP
.IP \(bu 2
Commit frequency over time.
.IP \(bu 2
Code churn (lines added vs deleted).
.IP \(bu 2
File hotspots (files that are modified most often).
.IP \(bu 2
Knowledge silos (files primarily owned by a single author).
.IP \(bu 2
Branch lifespans.
.PP
You can filter these metrics globally or by individual author directly in the web dashboard.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-port\fR \fIPORT\fR
Port to run the web server on (default: 8080)
.TP
\fB\-p\fR, \fB\-\-path\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the git repository folder (default: ./)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Prints detailed help information and examples.
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Prints the current version.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
.B Analyze the current directory and start the web server on the default port (8080):
.IP
$ GitAnalyser
.PP
.B Analyze a specific repository folder and start the web server on port 3000:
.IP
$ GitAnalyser \-\-path /home/user/projects/my-repo \-\-port 3000
.SH AUTHOR
Google Labs Jules
